state: S0: Connection attempt seen, no reply
S2: Connection established and close attempt by originator seen (but no reply from responder)
S3: Established, Resp attempts close, no reply from Orig
RSTO: Connection established, originator aborted (sent a RST)
RSTOS0: Originator sent a SYN followed by a RST, we never saw a SYN-ACK from the responder

code: RSTOSH."RSTOSH: Responder sent a SYN ACK followed by a RST
state: we never saw a SYN from the (purported) originator"
SH: Originator sent a SYN followed by a FIN, we never saw a SYN ACK from the responder (hence the connection was "half" open)
OTH: No SYN seen, just midstream traffic (a partial connection that was not later closed)
